I am curious about the phrase "distribute internally" - surely under GPL,
that is still distribution and all modifications should thus be made
public?  The GPL does not distinguish between "internal" distribution and
any other kind.

Soren, another possibility (and IANAL!) is to dual license your package
like say Rstudio which has an open source and commercial versions each with
different licences (doesn't it?).  This of course depends on your code
dependencies - i.e. afaik it can't link tightly to GPL code to do this -
but it can loosely.

Sean


